Defendant Georgette Camilla Martinez in court with attorney Dennis Schertz.  Aaron B Marcoux appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court addresses DEF as to waiving atty/client priviledge (prior attorney). Recess at 2:15 PM for atty/client conference. ON the record at 2:20 PM
Court addresses DEF re waiver of priviledge. Court  finds DEF is waiving right of priviledge freely and intelligently. State: no objections.
DEF calls Atty Moldenhauer. Mr Moldehauer sworn/testifies. Direct by Atty Scherz. Exhibit A given to Mr Moldenhauer. Direct. No objections by State. Exhibit A accepted by court.
Exhibit B given to Mr Moldenhauer. No objections by State. Direct. Exhibit B accepted by court. 
Exhibit D given to Mr Moldenhauer. Direct. No objections by State. Direct. Exhibit D accepted by court. 
Exhibit E given to Mr Moldenhauer. Direct. No objections by State. Exhibit E accepted by court.
State gives cross examination. No rebuttle.
DEF calls DEF Ms Martinez. DEF sworn/testifies. Direct by DEF. Cross examination by State. Court addresses parties. State tenders witness.
DEF: redirect. State: nothing further. DEF: no other witnesses. State: no other witnesses. Court: Evidence is closed. 
DEF argues insufficient counsel, right of allocution. State argues right of allocution was given. DEF argues re: prejudicial. State argues does not meet burden to be prejudicial. DEF: rebuttle. 
Court finds: is deficient performance that counsel did not keep track of notes. Court finds it is not prejudicial. 
State: argues if anyone is deficient, may be Atty Rafferty. State does not necessarily object to reopen evidence.
DEF argues deficency. Request to reopen evidence and call Atty Rafferty. 
3:47 PM Off the record. 3:57 PM ON the record. 4:02 PM Atty Rafferty calls into court. Sworn/testifies. DEF direct. State: cross.  DEF: no re-direct.
DEF: argues for deficient performance. State argues against. DEF: rebuttle. 
Court finds testimony between Mr Moldenhauer & DEF is not equivical. There is circumstantial evidence through Atty Rafferty that attempt was made get information regarding changing attorneys.
Court finds there was deficient performance in that an adjournment was not requested. Prejudicial? 
Court adresses parties re Judge Wright's sentence and rational. 
DEF unable to make argument of probability of Atty Rafferty to bring about different outcome.
State: argues unable to know outcome, isn't prejudicial.
Court finds it was deficient, but does not find that it is prejudicial. Motion denied.
DEF argues: for resentencing for interest of justice. Court had sufficiently addresses right of allocution.
DEF: argues def was not afforded complete discussion of PSI. Court addresses DEF regarding any inaccurancies. State argues def knew information in PSI, had timely receipt of PSI. No rebuttle.
Court denies motion. No evidence shown today that there were any inaccuracies in PSI.
Atty Schertz to prepare order.
and Order to Sheriff - copies to Sh. Dept.
